        <h1>Welcome to the NDEx Prototype Site</h1>

        <p>
          This site provides a preview of the functionality of NDEx, the
          Network Data Exchange.
        </p>

        <p>
          NDEx will be an open-source, web-based software system to enable
          individuals, groups, and software applications to share, store,
          manipulate, and publish biological network knowledge.
        </p>

        <p>
          While this prototype site will allow users to create accounts and
          upload networks, this site and its underlying database are not
          guaranteed to be stable or persistent. If you create an account and
          upload content, that content may not be present when you return to the
          site - during the development process, we will occasionally need to
          re-create and reload the test database.
        </p>

        <p>
          If you encounter problems using this prototype site, you can report
          them to <a href="mailto:dexter@ndexbio.org?Subject=NDEx%20Issue" target="_top">Dexter Pratt</a>.
          We would especially appreciate an email if you encounter any situation
          in which the site becomes inoperable.
        </p>

        <p>
          NDEx is a project of the <a href="http://www.cytoscape.org" target="_blank">Cytoscape Consortium</a>
          in conjunction with the <a href="http://www.idekerlab.ucsd.edu" target="_blank">Ideker Lab at the UCSD School of Medicine.</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          Learn more about NDEx at the <a href="http://ndexbio.org" target="_blank">NDEx Project Site.</a>
        </p>

        <p>
          Techincal details for NDEx are documented at the <a href="http://www.github.com/cytoscape/NDEx-Site/wiki" target="_blank">NDEx Github Repository Wiki.</a>
